descr: "A group of related requests that can be used to capture intended activities that have inter-dependencies such as \"give this medication after that one\"."

fields.name: resourceType
fields.descr: "This is a RequestGroup resource"

fields.name: identifier
fields.descr: "Allows a service to provide a unique, business identifier for the request."

fields.name: basedOn
fields.descr: "A plan, proposal or order that is fulfilled in whole or in part by this request."

fields.name: replaces
fields.descr: "Completed or terminated request(s) whose function is taken by this new request."

fields.name: groupIdentifier
fields.descr: "A shared identifier common to all requests that were authorized more or less simultaneously by a single author, representing the identifier of the requisition, prescription or similar form."

fields.name: status
fields.descr: "The current state of the request. For request groups, the status reflects the status of all the requests in the group."

fields.name: subject

fields.name: context

fields.descr: "Indicates the reason the request group was created. This is typically provided as a parameter to the evaluation and echoed by the service, although for some use cases, such as subscription- or event-based scenarios, it may provide an indication of the cause for the response."

fields.descr: "Indicates the reason the request group was created. This is typically provided as a parameter to the evaluation and echoed by the service, although for some use cases, such as subscription- or event-based scenarios, it may provide an indication of the cause for the response."
